{
  "texts": [
    "ML in bioinformatics refers to using ML techniques to analyze and interpret biological data, including genomics, systems biology, text mining, microarrays, and evolution.",
    "By applying ML algorithms to complex biological data sets, researchers can gain insights into various biological processes, identify genetic mutations, and even develop new disease treatments [34,35].",
    "ML can be applied through various modes of human-made database reports to process and evaluate data, decreasing labor expenses and fastening the research procedure without compromising quality [36,37].",
    "ML text evaluation can be utilized in bioinformatics as well.",
    "The containing of ML has given bioinformatics the needed promotion [38,39]."
  ]
}